# Differentiation against prior work

Side-by-side comparison of this research against prior work, broken down by aspect, to
make novelty visible.

## Differentiation matrix

| Aspect | [Prior A] | [Prior B] | [Prior C] | **This research** |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Period | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| Universe | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| Frequency (timeframe) | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| Method (model type) | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| Features / factors | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| Intervention / decision rule | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| Evaluation metric | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| Robustness checks | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| Claim / conclusion | ... | ... | ... | ... |
| Resource / deployment assumptions | ... | ... | ... | ... |

## Novelty check

The "this research" column must contain **at least one cell that is clearly distinct** from
the prior columns.

Levels:

| Level | Examples |
|---|---|
| Strong | New mathematical model / new ML architecture / new evaluation metric |
| Medium | Existing method on new data or universe / a novel combination of known methods |
| Weak | Different parameters / different period / reimplementation of the same method |

A research project that only achieves "weak" tends to become a degraded reimplementation.
Aim for "medium" or higher.

## Example

| Aspect | Smith et al. (2021) | Lee & Patel (2023) | **This research** |
|---|---|---|---|
| Period | 2016-2020 | 2018-2022 | (your period) |
| Universe | Public benchmark datasets | Field deployment logs | (your universe) |
| Frequency | Monthly batches | Event-level records | (your timeframe) |
| Method | Hierarchical model + ablation | Matched comparison design | (your method) |
| Features | Measurement covariates | Context labels | (your features) |
| Intervention / decision rule | Fixed threshold | Human-reviewed threshold | (your rule) |
| Metrics | Accuracy, calibration error | Reliability score | (your metrics) |
| Robustness | Per-cohort, ablation | Per-site replication | (your robustness) |
| Claim | Method improves calibration | Effect replicates in field logs | (your claim) |
| Resource / deployment assumptions | batch review | not specified | (your assumptions) |

## Notes

- Do not list only the aspects that favor this research; include unfavorable ones too
- Cite prior work concretely (author / year / venue)
- If the only differences are "weak", redesign the research
